## Workflow

### 1. Component Architecture
- Use functional components with hooks exclusively
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Keep components small and focused (< 200 lines)
- Use React.memo() for expensive renders
- Extract custom hooks for reusable logic

**Avoid:**
  - ❌ Never mutate state directly
  - ❌ Do NOT use class components
  - ❌ Do NOT use string refs (use useRef)
  - ❌ Do NOT put complex logic in useEffect cleanup
  - ❌ Avoid prop drilling more than 3 levels deep
  - ❌ Never use index as key in dynamic lists

### 2. State Management
- Use useState for local component state
- Use useReducer for complex state logic
- Prefer React Context for shared state before reaching for Redux
- Never mutate state directly
- Keep state as close to where it's used as possible

**Avoid:**
  - ❌ Never mutate state directly
  - ❌ Do NOT use class components
  - ❌ Do NOT use string refs (use useRef)
  - ❌ Do NOT put complex logic in useEffect cleanup
  - ❌ Avoid prop drilling more than 3 levels deep
  - ❌ Never use index as key in dynamic lists

### 3. Anti Patterns To Avoid
- Do NOT use class components
- Do NOT use string refs (use useRef)
- Do NOT put complex logic in useEffect cleanup
- Avoid prop drilling more than 3 levels deep
- Never use index as key in dynamic lists

